title: How have influenza vaccination rates in over 65 year olds changed?
analysis_commentary: The overall trend for the coverage of individuals aged over 65 receiving the influenza vaccination remains fairly static at between 70% and 75% over the time period recorded.
data_source: NHS England & Public Health England & Health & Social Care Information Centre
